title: Encoding and decoding arbitrary files from DNS TXT records
---

Back in September I had this idea, to encode files into DNS TXT records to be stored (ostensibly) without taking up disk space.[^1] I tested and implemented the idea on my then-employer's DNS server, hosting a PNG of their logo in TXT records at logo.\<employer\>.com.au, but have moved the example for this to logo.suv.id.au for obvious reasons. My implementations for this can be found on my [gist](https://gist.github.com/blha303/b751c5fed24f7cfdb206e220023fe053), but a short demo is below

[^1]: Obviously DNS records do in fact take up disk space somewhere, but if your DNS is hosted with some big provider that's entirely abstracted away from you ^_^


```python
import dns.resolver
q = dns.resolver.query("logo.suv.id.au","TXT").response.answer[0]
for line in sorted(_.strings[0] for _ in q)[:5]:
    print((line[:20] + b"..." + line[-20:]) if len(line) > 20 else line)
```

    b'{0000}iVBORw0KGgoAAA...pYPC/JLqiJrYPZjGUjsH'
    b'{0001}mH0pIKQFfwvN8R...yLgv+r3mfg0FgOr52dhT'
    b'{0002}QsSJps9VSwYtH4...7+IX/vcTyPKAh3cr6efq'
    b'{0003}yH09Nu9ySym8jX...a/1EC5eKJ/DakZM4PjoN'
    b'{0004}CF9vMC+UA35i6U...t4DoOvvPEM/B9lxfbY8F'



```python
from IPython.display import HTML
out = b""
for line in sorted(_.strings[0] for _ in q):
    if chr(line[0]) == "{":
        try:
            out += line.split(b"}",1)[1]
        except IndexError:
            pass
HTML("<img src='data:image/png;base64,{0}'/>".format(out.decode('utf-8')))
```




<img src='data:image/png;base64,'/>




```python
hwg = dns.resolver.query("hwg.suv.id.au","TXT").response.answer[0]
for line in sorted(_.strings[0] for _ in hwg)[:5]:
    print((line[:20] + b"..." + line[-20:]) if len(line) > 20 else line)
```

```python
out = b""
for line in sorted(_.strings[0] for _ in hwg):
    if chr(line[0]) == "{":
        try:
            out += line.split(b"}",1)[1]
        except IndexError:
            pass
HTML("<audio controls><source src='data:audio/mpeg;base64,{0}'/></audio>".format(out.decode('utf-8')))
```
